<TITLE> Cabinet approves renewable energy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh will produce five percent of the required electricity from renewable energy by 2015 and 10 percent by 2020, the interim cabinet decided on Wednesday. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed chaired the meeting that approved the renewable energy regulation, chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim said. "The regulation will fetch the country five percent of the required power from the renewable energy by 2015 and 10 percent by 2020 with the main sources being solar energy, wind energy, biogas and hydraulic energy," Munaim said. A sustainable energy development agency involving businesspeople, stakeholders, NGOs and experts will be set up under the policy. "Both public and private entrepreneurs in the sector will enjoy a five-year corporate tax exemption," Munaim said. The revised Private Universities Ordinance-2008 got final approval. The Bangla Academy Ordinance-2008 was also okayed in the meeting, he said, mentioning that according to the ordinance, the president of the country will be the chief patron of academy. The Trademark Ordinance-2008 was also given the nod at the advisory council meeting allowing maximum 150 days to get patent registration, the press secretary said. Bangladesh Better Business Forum recently asked for 30 days to register for patents. The meeting also provisionally endorsed the Bangladesh National Olympic Committee Ordinance -2008 but the proposed Bangladesh Parjatan (Tourism) Ordinance-2008 was sent back to the tourism ministry for further scrutiny. bdnews24.com
